# 1. キラキラ、青春！

Saki & Tsukasa: Leeet's eat! Let's eat!
Saki: Hm! The scrambled eggs have a different texture to them today!
Tsukasa: Yes, they seem fluffier for some reason.
Mother: Oh, you noticed? I tried mixing in a little mayonnaise today. That apparently helps make them a bit fluffier.
Saki: So that's what it is! These are great! They're so fluffy and full of flavor♪
Commercial: <This Moment With You!>
Saki: Oh...
Commercial: <Lemonade-flavored FizzYum Cider is only available for a limited time! Let's go out there and enjoy our youth together!>
Tsukasa: Oh, Saki, it's your band's song!
Mother: I don't think I'm ever going to get tired of this one.
Saki: Hehe♪ We have to thank Ichi for putting so much effort into it!
Saki: It really is a beautiful expression of youth, isn't it?!
Mother: Hehe. Yes, it is. Also...
Mother: I couldn't be happier about your band's song being used for this commercial. You've been watching this company's ads since you were little.
Saki: Mom...
Tsukasa: Yes, this is indeed a momentous occasion.
Tsukasa: You're back in school, just like in this commercial, having fun and enjoying your youth.... *Sob*
Saki: S-Stop it, Tsukasa! Don't cry!
Saki: Still, hearing our song on TV really does make it feel like we're pros now.
Saki: Hehe. We need to do our best at Jam Fest, too!
Mother: Speaking of which, Saki, do you have practice today?
Saki: Oh, that's right! Today we're meeting with our company, then having practice until the evening.
Saki: I probably won't be home until really late, so go ahead and have dinner without me.
Tsukasa: Alright, good luck! We'll be cheering you on, Saki!
Saki: Thanks!
Saki: Whoa, look at the time! I'm gonna be late if I don't go now!
Tsukasa: Saki! You'll choke if you scarf down your food like that! You should take smaller bites and chew carefully!
Saki: Thanks for breakfast! Gotta go!
Mother: Okay, stay safe.
Saki: ...is what happened! My mom and Tsukasa got all teary-eyed on me earlier this morning!
Honami: Hehe. They never change.
Shiho: It's the same over at my house. Every time that commercial comes on, Shizuku locks right onto my face...
Ichika: My dad also keeps shouting, “It's Ichika's song!”
Miku: They really can't contain their excitement.
Luka: Hehe. Yes, but I suppose that's only natural for your families to feel that way. They've been supporting you all this time.
Luka: They're likely happier than anyone to see you girls going pro together.
Shiho: Yeah, I guess.
Shiho: Then, that means we gotta make the most of their support by doing well at Jam Fest.
Honami: Agreed. Especially since it's going to be our first show since going pro. I'm sure that many of our most loyal fans will be there as well.
Ichika: Yeah, I definitely want to put on a good show for them.
Rin: While we're on the subject, what's Jam Fest actually supposed to be like? We know that it's one of those events where lots of different bands perform...
Ichika: Umm... Jam Fest is similar to most other music festivals. There's going to be several big stages where bands will be performing simultaneously.
Ichika: This event will have three stages.
Ichika: The most famous bands will be performing on the main stage, up-and-coming bands on the sub stage...
Ichika: And the one we'll be playing at is the rookie stage, which is for bands that have just debuted.
Ichika: The guests are free to move between those three stages and see whichever bands they like.
MEIKO: Oh, having so many stages to choose from sounds like a lot of fun!
KAITO: It sounds like people from all walks of life will be attending...
Shiho: Yes, that's usually the case. But most will be there to watch the main stage, so I'm not sure how many will be interested in seeing us.
Shiho: However, I did hear that STANDOUT and anemone will also be performing on the rookie stage.
Shiho: So we'll need to put on a good performance. Can't let them show us up.
Honami: I agree. Which means we need to get in a good practice today!
Ichika, Saki & Shiho: Yeah!
